* help_didyoumean_regression.dts
* HELP unknown-topic feedback + did-you-mean suggestions (AIF-047 M1-M3).
*
* Proves the HELP command owns its miss: an unknown topic yields an explicit
* "No help found for: X" line plus soundex/edit-distance suggestions (no more the
* self-referential "Type HELP X for more information" loop), and HELP GIANT <unknown>
* shares the same terminal. Also confirms SOUNDEX() still works after sharing its
* implementation with the suggester.
*
* Expected (grep between BEGIN/END):
*   No help found for: GAINT
*     Did you mean: GIANT, ...
*   No help found for: SELCT
*     Did you mean: SELECT, ...
*   No help found for: GAINT           (via HELP GIANT GAINT)
*   G530                               (SOUNDEX("GIANT"))
*
* Read-only; opens/mutates nothing.
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN HELP_DIDYOUMEAN
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/help_didyoumean_regression.dts

SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

FORMULA "HELP-DIDYOUMEAN-REGRESSION-BEGIN"
FORMULA "unknown topic -> not-found + did-you-mean (expect GIANT):"
HELP GAINT
FORMULA "another typo (expect SELECT):"
HELP SELCT
FORMULA "HELP GIANT <unknown> shares the not-found terminal:"
HELP GIANT GAINT
FORMULA "SOUNDEX() still works after sharing its implementation (expect G530):"
? SOUNDEX("GIANT")
FORMULA "HELP-DIDYOUMEAN-REGRESSION-END"
